<h1>Wood Skylights</h1>
Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup>Â skylights are available in custom wood interiors. Wood skylights pair the beauty of classic wood interiors with the durability and dependability of aluminum exteriors. Moldings and trims on the interior can be formed to match existing architectural elements on your house.

Thermal efficiency tends to be higher with a wooden skylight because wood allows for lower U-values. The lowered U-value means that the room will maintain a more even temperature and will not lose as much heat in the cold winter months. All of Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> systems are thermally isolated which prevents the metal frame from touching the glass at any point.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-37651" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/wood-skylight-interior.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Wood Interiors</h2>
Wood interiors can be composed of a solid wood or glulam interior and maintenance free aluminum exterior.Â Our advanced aluminum weep system carries water and condensation away from the wood, which increases the longevity of wood skylights.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-37652" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/wood-skylight2.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Staining</h2>
Owners can stain the structure themselves if they would like or Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> can complete the staining using a 3-5 coat microporous sealer. The first coat seals/protects the wood. The second coat stains the wood and the third coat is a finishing coat.Â With the addition of decorative trims and other accessories, the potential of Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> wood systems are limitless.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_tabs style="flat" shape="square" active_section="1"][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-info-circle" add_icon="true" title="Product Overview" tab_id="1502717567024-6ef4a3b9-ed9a"][vc_column_text]<a href="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/SI5006-Fixed-Skylight-Cut-Sheet.pdf"><img class="alignright wp-image-25556 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/coverpage1.png" alt="" width="400" height="248" /></a>Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> offers fixed skylights in virtually any size and can accommodate a wide range of configurations, including single slope, pyramids, segmented radius domes, barrel vault, hip end, glass roofs, roof lanterns, and more. These skylight systems can attach to virtually any substrate and are suited for both residential and commercial applications without size or design limitations. Skylights have several unique delivery options including Pre-Assembled Pre-Glazed, Pre-Assembled Not Pre-Glazed, and Knocked Down.
